Span.Text: Visualise data to gain better insights and prioritise more effectively to improve outcomes across your whole organisation.

“With Microsoft BI tools we have a global view of the services we provide. We can drill down and have a single view of an individual family and all of the transactions that take place around a given address. It’s an enabling platform, and we can do things now fairly simply that we wouldn’t have dreamed of in the past.”
Marlo Valente, Head of Enterprise Services, Leicester City Council

Use business intelligence tools to visualize data and gain insights for better decision making e.g. determine the effects of funding on things such as crime statistics, job creation, citizen engagement, and pollution.

Everything from energy, water, transportation fleets, personnel, and buildings—with analysis tools and key performance indicators (KPIs) that enable you to spot trends that can help control costs, reduce waste, drive new efficiencies, and streamline overall operations.

Using an aggregated view of case work and capacity you can prioritise resource allocation to those most in need, ensuring an optimum outcome for citizens.  Addressing most at risk cases sooner, minimises the possibility of escalation and impact on future resourcing.
